Domain management commands.

USAGE:
  scw container domain <command>

AVAILABLE COMMANDS:
  create      Create a new custom domain for the container with the specified ID.
  delete      Delete the custom domain associated with the specified ID.
  get         Get the custom domain associated with the specified ID.
  list        List all custom domains the caller can access (read permission).
  update      Update the domain associated with the specified ID.

FLAGS:
  -h, --help                help for domain
      --list-sub-commands   List all subcommands

GLOBAL FLAGS:
  -c, --config string    The path to the config file
  -D, --debug            Enable debug mode
  -o, --output string    Output format: json or human, see 'scw help output' for more info (default "human")
  -p, --profile string   The config profile to use

Use "scw container domain [command] --help" for more information about a command.
